{"id": "EUVD-2025-14110", "enisaUuid": "64122d2d-fd78-3708-941f-c28802d652fd", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\num: work around sched_yield not yielding in time-travel mode\n\nsched_yield by a userspace may not actually cause scheduling in\ntime-travel mode as no time has passed. In the case seen it appears to\nbe a badly implemented userspace spinlock in ASAN. Unfortunately, with\ntime-travel it causes an extreme slowdown or even deadlock depending on\nthe kernel configuration (CONFIG_UML_MAX_USERSPACE_ITERATIONS).\n\nWork around it by accounting time to the process whenever it executes a\nsched_yield syscall.", "datePublished": "2025-05-09T09:33:20", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-12T21:31:03", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/da780c4a075ba2deb05ae29f0af4a990578c7901", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/990ddc65173776f1e01e7135d8c1fd5f8fd4d5d2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/887c5c12e80c8424bd471122d2e8b6b462e12874", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-37880"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-37880"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "405b4616-67c4-39ae-b99a-95cbe683df8e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15-rc1"}, {"id": "6cb6499c-277c-3667-b5ae-1947b50d80d4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.26"}, {"id": "7a8b7647-f2eb-3be5-a371-999beef688d5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <887c5c12e80c8424bd471122d2e8b6b462e12874"}, {"id": "af6766c3-2234-3ecc-82a9-b0d4f707d33f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14.5"}, {"id": "c536390f-effa-3431-a48b-e88a23f3919d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <da780c4a075ba2deb05ae29f0af4a990578c7901"}, {"id": "e80d450d-bbf3-3bb5-90f1-58304e0d3856", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 